text:
Set in the 1990s, Captain Marvel follows Danvers, an Air Force officer, as she becomes one of the universe's most powerful heroes after earth gets involved in a galactic war between alien. The film is directed by Anna Boden and Ryan Fleck, who also wrote the script with Geneva Robertson-Dworet.
The trailer offers a look at Danvers' origin story, showcasing her transformation into Captain Marvel and her early days as a hero. We also get glimpses of Jude Law as Mar-Vell, a Kree warrior who trains Carol Danvers; Ben Mendelsohn as Talos, the leader of the Skrulls; and Annette Bening as the Supreme Intelligence, an artificial intelligence that serves as the ruler of the Kree Empire.
As for the cat, Goose, it appears to be an important part of the film, judging from the trailer. Goose is reportedly a Flerken, an alien creature that takes on a cat-like appearance.

Captain Marvel hits theaters on March 8, 2019.assistant

Here's a summary of the article:

Marvel has released a new trailer for the upcoming superhero movie "Captain Marvel", starring Brie Larson as Carol Danvers/Captain Marvel. The film is set in the 1990s and follows Danvers' origin story as she becomes one of the universe's most powerful heroes after Earth gets caught up in a galactic war between alien species. The trailer shows Danvers' transformation into Captain Marvel, as well as glimpses of other characters, including Jude Law as Mar-Vell, Ben Mendelsohn as Talos, and Annette Bening as the Supreme Intelligence.
